results.title: Live, Laugh, Love, Daisy Quilt, Couch Throw
results.description:
Few images are more wholesome than daisies in a mason jar! Along with this beautiful quote of "live, laugh, love." While a quilt can guarantee happiness, spending a few minutes under the awesome minky fabric and beautiful design sure can help!

This project uses Shannon Minky which is a high quality minky fabric that maintains its plush softness even after many washes. It can be difficult to construct with, but with patience and precision, the outcome is worth it! 

All my quilts use Heirloom Batting which is 80% cotton 20% Polyester. This batting provides a nice loft, while also having the breathability of cotton, and the long wear last of polyester. 

The binding is hand sewn, and the Long-Arm Quilting designs are custom to each project and done by Jil Mistic.

Washing and Care: All of my projects use high quality cotton and minky fabrics that are safe to spot treat and won’t run when washed. To increase the longevity of the quilt, I recommend washing in cold water, and tumble drying on low, however they can withstand warm temp washing and drying as well!

results.title: Live, Laugh, Lover poker work key ring/handbag charm German/English with crocheted gift bag
results.description:
„He achieved success who has lived well, laughed often, and loved much”

The first line of Bessie Anderson Stanley’s poem, Success, provides the inspiration for this key ring.
The English text “Live, Laugh, Love” is on one side and the German “Leben, Lachen, Lieben” on the other. I hope it will also inspire you. 
To make it particularly special, it comes with a hand-crocheted gift bag - ideal for Valentine's Day

The design/text are worked in poker work (pyrography) - burned into the wood and then sealed with varnish.
The key ring is 3-5cm in diameter. The square bag is worked in heavy cotton thread and measures approx. 10cm x 10cm. It can be reused for storing jewelry or other small articles.

Please be aware that as every wooden disc is different, each key ring is unique. The discs are slices of natural wood. Some still have bark attached. They vary in color and shape.
